            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2296,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01NNVSUAA3d2iZrdJMJWNAi4\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Let me break down what makes these keywords effective for your scheduling tool:\\n\\n**High Intent + Relevance:**\\nThe best keywords match what your target audience is actively searching for when they have a problem to solve. For a scheduling tool, people searching \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\" or \\\"find meeting times across time zones\\\" are already thinking about solutions—they're ready to buy.\\n\\n**Specificity Matters:**\\n- \\\"meeting scheduling tool\\\" is better than just \\\"scheduling\\\" because it's specific to your product category\\n- \\\"find meeting times across time zones\\\" directly addresses your core value proposition—it's what your tool *does*\\n- \\\"best meeting scheduler for remote teams\\\" targets your exact audience (remote teams) + their need (scheduling)\\n\\n**Search Intent Alignment:**\\nYour keywords should match three types of intent:\\n1. **Transactional** (ready to buy): \\\"meeting scheduling tool,\\\" \\\"automated calendar availability tool\\\"\\n2. **Problem-focused** (searching for solutions): \\\"find meeting times across time zones,\\\" \\\"cross timezone meeting planner\\\"\\n3. **Audience-specific** (targeting your market): \\\"best meeting scheduler for remote teams\\\"\\n\\n**Why the rejected keywords didn't work:**\\nKeywords like \\\"calendar coordination software\\\" and \\\"team scheduling automation\\\" are too generic and don't capture the specific pain point your tool solves. They also compete with broader, more established products. Your approved keywords (\\\"meeting scheduling tool,\\\" \\\"find meeting times across time zones\\\") are more direct and less competitive.\\n\\n**The sweet spot:** Keywords that combine your solution type + the specific problem you solve + your target audience = higher click-through rates and better conversion rates.\\n\\nDoes this help clarify the strategy? Which of the three new keywords I suggested resonate most with you?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3036,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":383,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
